01:22:01.920 --> 01:22:04.920
Felly, roeddwn yn cael ychwanegol

01:22:04.920 --> 01:22:07.920
ychwanegol yma,

01:22:07.920 --> 01:22:10.920
a'u gweld yn y carau,

01:22:10.920 --> 01:22:13.920
i gael ei gwasanaeth.

01:22:13.920 --> 01:22:16.920
Roeddwn yn cael ychwanegol

01:22:16.920 --> 01:22:19.920
ac roeddwn yn mynd arall ar y ffatri

01:22:19.920 --> 01:22:22.920
a'r holl ffatri

01:22:22.920 --> 01:22:25.920
ar y lles ymgyrch.

01:22:25.920 --> 01:22:28.920
Mae'r gwaith yn cael

01:22:28.920 --> 01:22:31.920
y botyls bach

01:22:31.920 --> 01:22:34.920
yn cael y botyls bach

01:22:34.920 --> 01:22:37.920
i ddod i'r carau.

01:22:37.920 --> 01:22:40.920
Roedd yn ffatri iawn i gyd yn gweithio.

01:22:40.920 --> 01:22:43.920
Ond…

01:22:43.920 --> 01:22:46.920
Do you think they were good employers on the whole?

01:22:46.920 --> 01:22:49.920
Yes. They were.

01:22:49.920 --> 01:22:52.920
Were there any other disputes

01:22:52.920 --> 01:22:55.920
that you were involved in?

01:22:55.920 --> 01:22:58.920
Well, we had to go when we wanted a pay rise

01:22:58.920 --> 01:23:01.920
and things like that, you know.

01:23:01.920 --> 01:23:04.920
And I can remember this

01:23:04.920 --> 01:23:07.920
boss,

01:23:07.920 --> 01:23:10.920
he was very nice

01:23:10.920 --> 01:23:13.920
and I felt awful sorry for him.

01:23:13.920 --> 01:23:16.920
But we were arguing

01:23:16.920 --> 01:23:19.920
the amount of money

01:23:19.920 --> 01:23:22.920
that we should have, you know,

01:23:22.920 --> 01:23:25.920
for doing the job and things like that.

01:23:25.920 --> 01:23:28.920
And I said,

01:23:28.920 --> 01:23:31.920
as far as I concerned,

01:23:31.920 --> 01:23:34.920
they're caught now.

01:23:34.920 --> 01:23:37.920
If they want to move,

01:23:37.920 --> 01:23:40.920
we go out on strike, you know.

01:23:40.920 --> 01:23:43.920
And anyway…

01:23:43.920 --> 01:23:46.920
he was going anyway.

01:23:46.920 --> 01:23:49.920
This broke and I went into the office

01:23:49.920 --> 01:23:52.920
and I said, I'm sorry to you that you're going.

01:23:52.920 --> 01:23:55.920
I said, better the devil you know

01:23:55.920 --> 01:23:58.920
than the devil you don't know like me, you know.

01:23:58.920 --> 01:24:01.920
He was very nice, he was the boss.

01:24:01.920 --> 01:24:04.920
Yeah.

01:24:04.920 --> 01:24:07.920
He let us out a bit anyway.

01:24:07.920 --> 01:24:10.920
But he didn't stay that long after.

01:24:10.920 --> 01:24:13.920
I felt awful sorry for him.

01:24:13.920 --> 01:24:16.920
So what period was this?

01:24:16.920 --> 01:24:19.920
What years are you talking about?

01:24:19.920 --> 01:24:22.920
Oh gosh. It's been a long time now.

01:24:22.920 --> 01:24:25.920
I think it was about

01:24:25.920 --> 01:24:28.920
three years before I left there.

01:24:28.920 --> 01:24:31.920
No, what I mean is when did you go and work there?

01:24:31.920 --> 01:24:34.920
Do you remember? And when did you leave?

01:24:34.920 --> 01:24:37.920
Well I went there when Stephen was 12.

01:24:37.920 --> 01:24:40.920
So that was 1970 something,

01:24:40.920 --> 01:24:43.920
I think it was.

01:24:43.920 --> 01:24:46.920
1978, 1979.

01:24:46.920 --> 01:24:49.920
I think it was anyway.

01:24:49.920 --> 01:24:52.920
It was…

01:24:52.920 --> 01:24:55.920
I think it was anyway.

01:24:55.920 --> 01:24:58.920
It was before the women could

01:24:58.920 --> 01:25:01.920
pay full stamp.

01:25:01.920 --> 01:25:04.920
Right.

01:25:04.920 --> 01:25:07.920
Because I said to the girls on the line, I said,

01:25:07.920 --> 01:25:10.920
you may as well pay full stamp now

01:25:10.920 --> 01:25:13.920
because you will get you know,

01:25:13.920 --> 01:25:16.920
money then when you all like on

01:25:16.920 --> 01:25:19.920
a sick or something.

01:25:19.920 --> 01:25:22.920
And they all agreed except one.

01:25:25.920 --> 01:25:28.920
She went then.

01:25:28.920 --> 01:25:31.920
She died no later.

01:25:31.920 --> 01:25:34.920
Part, we're all part.

01:25:34.920 --> 01:25:37.920
But yeah,

01:25:37.920 --> 01:25:40.920
they all went and done it, you know.

01:25:40.920 --> 01:25:43.920
That was before I went on the union of course.

01:25:43.920 --> 01:25:46.920
But I said you should leave you darling.

01:25:46.920 --> 01:25:49.920
So what do you think?

01:25:49.920 --> 01:25:52.920
Because it seemed to me you were

01:25:52.920 --> 01:25:55.920
a shy young woman and you became…

01:25:55.920 --> 01:25:58.920
I was really…

01:25:58.920 --> 01:26:01.920
I came out of my shell really.

01:26:01.920 --> 01:26:04.920
And why do you think that was?

01:26:04.920 --> 01:26:07.920
I don't know because I could see somebody was doing other people down, you know.

01:26:07.920 --> 01:26:10.920
And

01:26:10.920 --> 01:26:13.920
being my father's child,

01:26:13.920 --> 01:26:16.920
I wouldn't have that, you know.

01:26:16.920 --> 01:26:19.920
And I thought he was terrible.

01:26:19.920 --> 01:26:22.920
But they got away with some of the things.

01:26:22.920 --> 01:26:25.920
You know.

01:26:25.920 --> 01:26:28.920
But then I got to sit back

01:26:28.920 --> 01:26:31.920
and shut up.

01:26:31.920 --> 01:26:34.920
But you enjoyed your time as union ref then?

01:26:34.920 --> 01:26:37.920
Oh yeah, yeah, yeah. I did.

01:26:37.920 --> 01:26:40.920
Are you still a member of GMB?

01:26:40.920 --> 01:26:43.920
They sent me a card and

01:26:43.920 --> 01:26:46.920
I don't know, they haven't sent me any since.

01:26:46.920 --> 01:26:49.920
Since 1996 I haven't used anything.

01:26:49.920 --> 01:26:52.920
Right.

01:26:52.920 --> 01:26:55.920
So I don't know if I've got to pay or not.

01:26:55.920 --> 01:26:58.920
You should have to pay if you're not…

01:26:58.920 --> 01:27:01.920
No, if you don't go in, I like.

01:27:01.920 --> 01:27:04.920
But my husband is.

01:27:04.920 --> 01:27:07.920
Oh right. You should be well.

01:27:07.920 --> 01:27:10.920
Can I just ask you

01:27:10.920 --> 01:27:13.920
a bit about

01:27:13.920 --> 01:27:16.920
the social life in the factories

01:27:16.920 --> 01:27:19.920
and

01:27:19.920 --> 01:27:22.920
in the factories now,

01:27:22.920 --> 01:27:25.920
did they arrange Christmas parties

01:27:25.920 --> 01:27:28.920
and that kind of thing? Yes.

01:27:28.920 --> 01:27:31.920
Which ones did?

01:27:31.920 --> 01:27:34.920
I think all of them did really.

01:27:34.920 --> 01:27:37.920
And where were they held? Do you remember?

01:27:37.920 --> 01:27:40.920
I know in Switchcare

01:27:40.920 --> 01:27:43.920
my brothers

01:27:43.920 --> 01:27:46.920
and sisters came to the

01:27:46.920 --> 01:27:49.920
parties that were there.

01:27:49.920 --> 01:27:52.920
So where were they held then?

01:27:52.920 --> 01:27:55.920
I haven't got a clue.

01:27:55.920 --> 01:27:58.920
Because my parents used to take them.

01:27:58.920 --> 01:28:01.920
Because you said you couldn't remember a canteen or anything?

01:28:01.920 --> 01:28:04.920
The canteen was outside.

01:28:04.920 --> 01:28:07.920
Oh outside you said, yeah.

01:28:07.920 --> 01:28:10.920
Yeah, it was a big canteen outside.

01:28:10.920 --> 01:28:13.920
We had to pass it to get into work.

01:28:13.920 --> 01:28:16.920
And was that it then? Was it just a Christmas do

01:28:16.920 --> 01:28:19.920
or were there other do's?

01:28:19.920 --> 01:28:22.920
And of course they used to have the float

01:28:22.920 --> 01:28:25.920
that goes around different valleys.

01:28:25.920 --> 01:28:28.920
Oh yeah, tell me about that.

01:28:28.920 --> 01:28:31.920
It was great.

01:28:31.920 --> 01:28:34.920
Tell me about the float then, what you did on the float.

01:28:34.920 --> 01:28:37.920
I think they'd done the float, the boys

01:28:37.920 --> 01:28:40.920
that were apprentices there then.

01:28:40.920 --> 01:28:43.920
And they'd done all the float.

01:28:43.920 --> 01:28:46.920
And I think we got

01:28:46.920 --> 01:28:49.920
in the back lorry then, which was a

01:28:49.920 --> 01:28:52.920
well, a type of lorry then.

01:28:52.920 --> 01:28:55.920
They'd done all that out

01:28:55.920 --> 01:28:58.920
and we were the choir that was

01:28:58.920 --> 01:29:01.920
in the back of the lorry.

01:29:01.920 --> 01:29:04.920
Describe the float to me.

01:29:04.920 --> 01:29:07.920
Well they had Father Christmas

01:29:07.920 --> 01:29:10.920
in his sleigh and reindeer.

01:29:10.920 --> 01:29:13.920
And then of course the choir

01:29:13.920 --> 01:29:16.920
was in the other one then.

01:29:16.920 --> 01:29:19.920
And they made that look fanciful as well.

01:29:19.920 --> 01:29:22.920
And what did this float used to do then?

01:29:22.920 --> 01:29:25.920
Where did you go?

01:29:25.920 --> 01:29:28.920
Well we went to Arbedale

01:29:28.920 --> 01:29:31.920
and places like that.

01:29:31.920 --> 01:29:34.920
You know, Ponty and all switching away.

01:29:34.920 --> 01:29:37.920
Blackwood, Markham.

01:29:37.920 --> 01:29:40.920
And so what did you do then?

01:29:40.920 --> 01:29:43.920
Well we sang carols.

01:29:43.920 --> 01:29:46.920
Right.

01:29:46.920 --> 01:29:49.920
And the boys from Scotland

01:29:49.920 --> 01:29:52.920
I couldn't understand them.

01:29:52.920 --> 01:29:55.920
We were just killing ourselves laughing.

01:29:55.920 --> 01:29:58.920
So Leonard, I was courting Leonard at the time.

01:29:58.920 --> 01:30:01.920
So we came up to

01:30:01.920 --> 01:30:04.920
one of the pubs on the way in.

01:30:04.920 --> 01:30:07.920
And I said, you've got to fetch me

01:30:07.920 --> 01:30:10.920
some socks, my feet are freezing.

01:30:10.920 --> 01:30:13.920
So you've brought me some socks.

01:30:13.920 --> 01:30:16.920
And yeah, they, whenever we stopped

01:30:16.920 --> 01:30:19.920
people gave us things, you know.

01:30:19.920 --> 01:30:22.920
They were marvellous.

01:30:22.920 --> 01:30:25.920
Were you raising money for any charity or something?

01:30:25.920 --> 01:30:28.920
I can't remember.

01:30:28.920 --> 01:30:31.920
Because we were at the back, you know,

01:30:31.920 --> 01:30:34.920
if they wanted to give something to Father Christmas they did.

01:30:34.920 --> 01:30:37.920
But mostly I think they were giving presents to them.

01:30:37.920 --> 01:30:40.920
The switch gear was giving presents to who?

01:30:40.920 --> 01:30:43.920
To the smaller children, you know.

01:30:43.920 --> 01:30:46.920
They were giving presents to the children.

01:30:46.920 --> 01:30:49.920
And did that used to happen every year?

01:30:49.920 --> 01:30:52.920
Yes.

01:30:52.920 --> 01:30:55.920
It sounds like quite an event.

01:30:55.920 --> 01:30:58.920
Yes.

01:30:58.920 --> 01:31:01.920
I don't think they do it now.

01:31:01.920 --> 01:31:04.920
You know, because the switch gear

01:31:04.920 --> 01:31:07.920
of course, like all the other factories.

01:31:07.920 --> 01:31:10.920
I mean I think they still work down there.

01:31:10.920 --> 01:31:13.920
There's some ships and things like that, you know.

01:31:16.920 --> 01:31:19.920
But every year they used to be out.

01:31:19.920 --> 01:31:22.920
Right.

01:31:22.920 --> 01:31:25.920
And they could see

01:31:25.920 --> 01:31:28.920
along the way, like, you know,

01:31:28.920 --> 01:31:31.920
the lights and everything.

01:31:31.920 --> 01:31:34.920
Beautiful.

01:31:34.920 --> 01:31:37.920
Were there lights on the stairs?

01:31:37.920 --> 01:31:40.920
There were lights everywhere. Beautiful.

01:31:43.920 --> 01:31:46.920
What about the camaraderie

01:31:46.920 --> 01:31:49.920
with the women in the factory?

01:31:49.920 --> 01:31:52.920
Oh, very good.

01:31:52.920 --> 01:31:55.920
In every one of them?

01:31:55.920 --> 01:31:58.920
Did you remain friends with people when you left?

01:31:58.920 --> 01:32:01.920
Yes. I got quite a few friends.

01:32:01.920 --> 01:32:04.920
Some of them had died, you know, and things like that.

01:32:04.920 --> 01:32:07.920
My friend now,

01:32:07.920 --> 01:32:10.920
I've got a pen for her.

01:32:10.920 --> 01:32:13.920
She's 60 next week.

01:32:13.920 --> 01:32:16.920
And I've got some paper

01:32:16.920 --> 01:32:19.920
and things and we wrap it up for her.

01:32:19.920 --> 01:32:22.920
So, yeah.

01:32:22.920 --> 01:32:25.920
All my friends are very good.

01:32:25.920 --> 01:32:28.920
Do you still see a lot of them?

01:32:28.920 --> 01:32:31.920
Yes. And do you go out and things?

01:32:31.920 --> 01:32:34.920
We don't now,

01:32:34.920 --> 01:32:37.920
but we used to at one time.

01:32:37.920 --> 01:32:40.920
We used to go out a lot, you know.

01:32:40.920 --> 01:32:43.920
Well, Carol,

01:32:43.920 --> 01:32:46.920
her first husband left her.

01:32:46.920 --> 01:32:49.920
And then

01:32:49.920 --> 01:32:52.920
the other one then, he died of cancer.

01:32:52.920 --> 01:32:55.920
And she met another boy

01:32:55.920 --> 01:32:58.920
and she's married him now,

01:32:58.920 --> 01:33:01.920
last year.

01:33:01.920 --> 01:33:04.920
And he's very nice.

01:33:04.920 --> 01:33:07.920
We all go on

01:33:07.920 --> 01:33:10.920
with our lives, don't we?

01:33:10.920 --> 01:33:13.920
Yes.

01:33:13.920 --> 01:33:16.920
Looking back now then,

01:33:16.920 --> 01:33:19.920
how do you feel about the time you've spent

01:33:19.920 --> 01:33:22.920
working in the factories?

01:33:22.920 --> 01:33:25.920
Good. Yeah.

01:33:26.920 --> 01:33:29.920
Is it something you'd do again?

01:33:29.920 --> 01:33:32.920
Yes.

01:33:32.920 --> 01:33:35.920
We even saved for a dog

01:33:35.920 --> 01:33:38.920
for the blind.

01:33:38.920 --> 01:33:41.920
And we had a picture prepped, you know,

01:33:41.920 --> 01:33:44.920
to say this is the dog

01:33:44.920 --> 01:33:47.920
and this is the person that is having the dog.

01:33:47.920 --> 01:33:50.920
Where was that?

01:33:50.920 --> 01:33:53.920
In Valiwors.

01:33:53.920 --> 01:33:56.920
Marvellous.

01:33:56.920 --> 01:33:59.920
Marvellous people.

01:33:59.920 --> 01:34:02.920
They'd give to anything.

01:34:02.920 --> 01:34:05.920
We had red nose day there, you know,

01:34:05.920 --> 01:34:08.920
and people were cutting their hair off

01:34:08.920 --> 01:34:11.920
and things like that, you know.

01:34:11.920 --> 01:34:14.920
And I was all in my break time.

01:34:14.920 --> 01:34:17.920
We went around as well with the box, you know,

01:34:17.920 --> 01:34:20.920
and the money.

01:34:20.920 --> 01:34:23.920
And you were in the factories.

01:34:23.920 --> 01:34:26.920
Was it still there when you retired

01:34:26.920 --> 01:34:29.920
as good as when you started?

01:34:29.920 --> 01:34:32.920
Yes.

01:34:32.920 --> 01:34:35.920
I think now my friend

01:34:35.920 --> 01:34:38.920
has said that

01:34:38.920 --> 01:34:41.920
it's entirely different.

01:34:41.920 --> 01:34:44.920
So I think I had the good times

01:34:44.920 --> 01:34:47.920
in the factory.

01:34:47.920 --> 01:34:50.920
And when did you retire?

01:34:50.920 --> 01:34:53.920
Oh, God.

01:34:53.920 --> 01:34:56.920
1995.

01:34:56.920 --> 01:34:59.920
So I've had a good time.

01:34:59.920 --> 01:35:02.920
On my husband.

01:35:02.920 --> 01:35:05.920
Yes.

01:35:05.920 --> 01:35:08.920
Because I said I want to retire.

01:35:08.920 --> 01:35:11.920
I'd done it about 52 and a half,

01:35:11.920 --> 01:35:14.920
something like that.

01:35:14.920 --> 01:35:17.920
I had four children,

01:35:17.920 --> 01:35:20.920
so I thought I'd done my lot.

